          "display_name": null,
          "email": "honghui_xiao@yeah.net",
          "username": "HongHuiXiao"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-03-13 03:23:14.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\n> The handling of patch 30027 \"spec for Container based network\n > service/function\" has set up a precedent of how we need to handle\n > our features in a fair and consistent way in our project.\n > \n > I understand the rationale of handling of 30027 is that:\n > \n > - The technical spec needs to be approved first\n > - If there are still comments on the technical specs, creation of\n > repo (if needed) cannot be approved. E.g. 30027 and its repo\n > creation request\n > - Logically, it implies that if there are still comments on the\n > technical specs, we need to hold on pushing the code (because even\n > repo cannot be approved).\n > \n > Based on above rationale, the same principle will be applied to all\n > of our features in a fair and consistent way.\n > \n > Thus I give -2 because the specs 28973 is not finished and approved\n > yet. The code review should be postponed after we finish and\n > approve the specs.\n\nSo, what is holding specs 28973?",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
